{"lemma":"خالِق","slug":"خالِق","root":"خ.ل.ق","root_slug":"خ-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خالِق","root":"خلق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11409"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D9%82"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"creative"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Creator, Maker (God)","examples":[{"text":"هُوَ ٱللّٰهُ ٱلْخَالِقُ ٱلْبَارِئُ ٱلْمُصَوِّرُ"},{"text":"The hot sun and stars, the earth with its wealth of life, are complete evidence that the origin of the universe has occurred in time, at a fixed point of time, and therefore the universe must have been created. A great First Cause, an eternal, all-knowing and all-powerful Creator must exist, and the universe if His handiwork.","english":"Origin of the World – By Chance or Design?"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inventor, maker, author"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of خَلَقَ (ḵalaqa, “to create”)."},"ipa":["/xaː.liq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11409","headword_ar":"خَالِقٌ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A worker in leather"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) because he measures first, and then cuts. (TA.) To"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAliqaAt","text_ar":"خَالِقَات"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning Women"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"working in leather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as engaged in dividing a hide ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adiym","text_ar":"اَدِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"), El-Kumeyt likens genealogists. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaAliqu","text_ar":"الخَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an epithet applied to God, (K, Msb, TA,) properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who brings into existence according to the proper measure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adaptation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Creator;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Originator, not after the similitude of anything pre-existing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who hath brought into existence all things after they had not been in existence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxal~aAqu","text_ar":"الخَلَّاقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (Msb, * TA;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Creator of all things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as an intensive epithet,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Great Creator;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Creator of many creatures:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh and Bd and Jel, in xxxvi. 81:) Az says that this epithet, with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", may not be applied to any but God. (Msb.) Accord. to IAmb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAraka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"تَبَارَكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosanu AlxaAliqiyna","text_ar":"اَحْسَنُ الخَالِقِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHsn Almuqad~ariyna","text_ar":"احسن المُقَدَّرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blessed be God, the Best of those who make things according to their proper measures,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adaptations"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","TA","Az"]}]}}